      "content": "Beyond ice and insects, the system can suffer from obstructions caused by foreign object damage or contamination. Sometimes, fine particulate matter, like dust or sand kicked up from the runway, can get lodged inside the tube, especially if the tube itself has any minor imperfections. Furthermore, damage to the tubing or the static ports themselves—perhaps from bird strikes or impact—can introduce leaks or blockages that aren't immediately obvious. It's a delicate system, so even small intrusions can cause a major reading discrepancy.",
